NetPanzer Map Editor (Qt5 port)
================================

0.1 (in development)
---------------------
- Complete rewrite from ClanLib+SCons+Ruby to Qt5+Meson+C++
- Proper binary .npm load/save with verified round-trip
- .opt (outpost) and .spn (spawn point) companion file support
- Tile painting with undo/redo (Command pattern, per-stroke batching)
- Object placement, selection, drag-to-move, rename, delete
- Tileset atlas rendering (QImage-based, palette-indexed .tls loader)
- Minimap dock with viewport overlay and click-to-pan
- Tile picker dock
- Zoom toward cursor
- 25 automated Qt Test unit tests (maploader + tlsloader)
- Meson build system with ASan/UBSan enabled by default
- AppImage packaging via linuxdeploy

--- Historical Flexlay releases ---

Flexlay 0.1.0
=============
 - splitted flexlay into a C++ library and a scripting modules, Ruby
   and (very limited) Python support is now available
 - restructured the scripting bindings
 - C++ object hierachy now completly available in scripting
 - switched build system from autohell to SCons
 - support for resizable rectangular objects
 - better support for sprite objects
 - support for constrained object movement
 - major GUI cleanup
 - a icon-toolbar
 - configurable keyboard shortcut support
 - SuperTux: support for multiple sublevels and most features of
   lasted development version
 - NetPanzer: support for object based level building, no more need to
   mess with raw tiles
 - Pingus: basic support for loading levels and saving them, however
   only limited editing capabilties
 - Paint: a simple paint application with support for animation

Flexlay 0.0.1
==============
 - first release
 - zoom support
 - multilayer tilemap support
 - tilemap to png converting
 - tile brushes
 - simple copy/paste
 - undo/redo
 - game object support
 - SuperTux support
 - netPanzer support
 - Windstille support
 - Pingus support (load only)

